Provincial authorities say members of the public in the Western Cape are not wearing their masks, practising social distancing and sanitising. eNCA's Ronald Masinda has more details on this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Western Cape authorities say some residents simply are not obeying COVID-19 regulations. They say members of the public are not wearing their masks, practising social distancing and sanitising. READ: SA Lockdown: COVID-19 regulations ignored in Soweto Police and other law enforcement officials have been out this weekend at some of the busiest areas in Cape Town, to enforce compliance. Some residents were issued fines for breaking Covid-19 regulations. Business owners were also penalised for not closing in time for the curfew.